comments.body:
[~mmunn1], the fix looks good to me. You would probably want to remove the existing "input.release( null )" call. An alternative fix would be to update AddressManager so we did not allocate an address when the user was out of quota, e.g. use:

{code}
  RestrictedTypes.allocateUnitlessResource( allocator );
{code}

rather than the existing:

{code}
  RestrictedTypes.allocateNamedUnitlessResources( 1, allocator, allocator ).get( 0 );
{code}

as allocateUnitlessResource would check the quota before allocating. I have not tried this alternative approach.
